      "content": "Here's a Python function to convert Keplerian elements to Cartesian coordinates:\n```python\nimport math\n\ndef kepler_to_cartesian(a, e, i, omega, w, nu):\n    \"\"\"\n    Convert Keplerian elements to Cartesian coordinates.\n\n    Args:\n        a (float): Semi-major axis.\n        e (float): Eccentricity.\n        i (float): Inclination in radians.\n        omega (float): Longitude of the ascending node in radians.\n        w (float): Argument of periapsis in radians.\n        nu (float): True anomaly in radians.\n\n    Returns:\n        tuple: (x, y, z) position in Cartesian coordinates.\n    \"\"\"\n    # Calculate eccentric anomaly\n    E = 2 * math.atan((1 - e) ** 0.5 * math.tan(0.5 * nu))\n    \n    # Calculate rectangular coordinates\n    cos_E = math.cos(E)\n    sin_E = math.sin(E)\n    cos_E Approx = math.cos(E - omega)\n    sin_E_Proj = math.sin(E - omega)\n    X = a * cos_E\n    Y = a * sin_E * math.cos(i)\n    Z = a * sin_E * math.sin(i)",
